Standards for Enterprise Application Hosting Services are as follows:


  No new departmental application deployments are to occur in data centres that are targeted for closure within two years;
  All departmental applications must have an application health rating in the Application Portfolio Management (APM) system of at least âMinimal attention requiredâ; 
  New departmental mainframe applications must be deployed in accordance to the GC Mainframe Strategy; and
  Departments must map all applications hosted on Shared Services Canada (SSC) infrastructure using the Application Portfolio Management application identification within the SSC-managed Configuration Management Database (CMDB).
